webLinks.linkText: MidCoast Council Emergency Road Closure Information

properties.headline: FLOODING - MIDCOAST COUNCIL - GLENTHORNE TO TAREE Manning River Drive on Martin Bridge over Manning River
properties.otherAdvice:
Martin Bridge on Manning River Drive at Taree has reopened to light vehicles (less then 20 tonnes), including school buses. 

Heavy vehicles can continue to access Taree through Cundletown. Further inspections will be carried out on the bridge in coming days before it opens to heavy vehicles.

properties.otherAdvice: This is a local road - please visit Wollondilly Shire Council website or social media channels for up to date information.

FLOODING - PALLAMALLAWA (EAST OF MOREE) Gwydir Highway between Grattai Road, Biniguy AND Terry Hie Hie Road, Rocky Creek
properties.diversions:
Eastbound via north onto Newell Hwy, then right to Back Pally Rd, Mosquito Creek Rd, Paramellowa St, right to River St, Grattai Rd to rejoin Gwydir Hwy. 
This diversion is suitable for vehicles up to 42 tonne.

Westbound diversion is the same in reverse.
